{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01467VxunbiGscnpFJ4w3NNG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive exploration report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase to understand how to implement a \"daemon status overview\" feature. Here's what I found:\n\n### Current Implementation Architecture\n\n**1. CLI Command Structure (`cmd/cloche/main.go`)**\n- Current commands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `loop`, `shutdown`, `health`, `project`, `tasks`, `workflow`, `validate`, `get`, `set`, `init`\n- Commands that require daemon connection (gRPC): `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `loop`, `shutdown`\n- Commands that don't need daemon: `init`, `health`, `get`, `set`, `tasks`, `workflow`, `validate`, `project`\n- Default daemon address: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` (environment: `CLOCHE_ADDR`)\n\n**2. gRPC Service Definition (`api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)**\n- Service: `ClocheService` with 13 RPCs\n- Key RPC for daemon status: `GetProjectInfo(GetProjectInfoRequest) -> GetProjectInfoResponse`\n- `GetProjectInfo` currently handles per-project info only\n- No daemon-wide status RPC exists yet\n\n**3. Current Status Command (`cmd/cloche/status <run-id>`)**\n- Uses `GetStatus(GetStatusRequest)` RPC to fetch single run state\n- Displays: Run ID, title, workflow, type (host/container), state, container ID, error, active step, step executions\n- Outputs in human-readable format with step execution details\n\n**4. Current List Command (`cloche list [flags]`)**\n- Uses `ListRuns(ListRunsRequest)` RPC\n- Filters: `--all`, `--project`, `--state`, `--limit`, `--issue`\n- Displays compact run summary table with run ID, workflow, state, type, title, container ID, error\n\n**5. Current Project Command (`cloche project [--name <label>]`)**\n- Uses `GetProjectInfo(GetProjectInfoRequest)` RPC\n- Per-project output showing:\n  - Config (active, concurrency, stagger, dedup, stop_on_error, evolution)\n  - Loop state (running/stopped/halted with halt error if applicable)\n  - Active runs count with details\n  - Container and host workflows\n\n**6. gRPC Server Implementation (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)**\n- `ClocheServer` struct maintains:\n  - `runIDs map[string]string` (run_id → container_id)\n  - `loops map[string]*host.Loop` (project_dir → orchestration loop)\n  - References to store, captures, logStore, container runtime, evolution trigger, log broadcaster\n- Key methods:\n  - `GetStatus()` - single run status (line 460-512)\n  - `ListRuns()` - filtered run listing (line 425-458)\n  - `GetProjectInfo()` - per-project info with config, workflows, active runs (line 1122-1236)\n  - `GetVersion()` - version info (line 1260-1262)\n  - `Shutdown()` - daemon shutdown with active run check (line 1264-1288)\n\n**7. RunStore Interface (`internal/ports/store.go`)**\n- Methods available:\n  - `ListProjects(ctx)` - all project directories with runs\n  - `ListRunsByProject(projectDir, since)` - runs filtered by project\n  - `ListRunsFiltered(filter)` - complex filtering\n- Store implementation: SQLite (`internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n\n**8. Domain Types (`internal/domain/run.go`)**\n- `RunState` constants: `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n- `Run` struct contains ID, workflow, state, active steps, step executions, project, error, container ID, base SHA, title, is_host, parent run ID, task ID\n- `StepExecution` struct with step name, result, timestamps, logs, git ref\n\n**9. Web Handler (`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)**\n- Routes available:\n  - `GET /` - project overview (all projects with health stats and recent runs)\n  - `GET /projects/{name}/runs` - project-specific runs\n  - `GET /runs` - all runs list\n  - `GET /api/projects` - JSON list of all projects\n  - `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` - project details\n  - `GET /api/runs/{id}` - run details JSON\n- `handleProjectOverview()` aggregates all projects with:\n  - Health calculation (pass/fail counts)\n  - Recent run history (last 10 runs)\n  - Active run count\n  - Project labels and directories\n\n**10. Configuration (`internal/config/config.go`)**\n- Per-project config: `active`, `daemon` (listen, HTTP, image, db, runtime, agent_path, llm_command), `evolution`, `orchestration` settings\n- Orchestration settings: `concurrency`, `stagger_seconds`, `list_tasks_command`, `dedup_seconds`, `stop_on_error`\n\n**11. Version System**\n- Version stored in `/workspace/internal/version/VERSION` (currently \"1.4.2\")\n- `GetVersion()` RPC returns version string\n- CLI `cloche -v` shows CLI, daemon, and agent versions\n\n### Key Files for Implementation\n\n- **Proto definition**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 1-169)\n- **gRPC server**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (1354 lines)\n- **CLI status command**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (cmdStatus at line 223)\n- **CLI project command**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/project.go` (cmdProject at line 14)\n- **CLI list command**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (cmdList at line 262)\n- **Domain types**: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (195 lines)\n- **Store interface**: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (60 lines)\n- **Config**: `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` (119 lines)\n- **Web handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1800+ lines)\n\n### Available Data for Daemon Status Overview\n\nFrom gRPC server and store, you can retrieve:\n1. **All projects** via `store.ListProjects()`\n2. **Per-project runs** via `store.ListRunsByProject(projectDir, since)`\n3. **Orchestration loops status** via `server.loops` map (active/halted/stopped)\n4. **Per-project config** via `config.Load(projectDir)`\n5. **Container runtime state** via `container.Inspect()` for running containers\n6. **Run aggregates**:\n   - Total runs, active runs, succeeded/failed/cancelled counts\n   - Health status (pass rate)\n   - Recent activity timeline\n7. **Agent/daemon/container image version** via existing GetVersion() RPC\n\n### Implementation Strategy Points\n\n1. **Proto addition needed**: New RPC like `GetDaemonStatus()` or `GetDaemonOverview()` returning daemon-wide metrics\n2. **gRPC server implementation**: Aggregates data across all projects from store and loop state\n3. **CLI command**: New command like `cloche daemon status` or `cloche status --all` that calls the new RPC\n4. **Help text pattern**: See `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` for all help text definitions (lines 8-425)\n5. **Output format patterns**: \n   - Human-readable: See `cmdProject()` format\n   - Compact table: See `cmdList()` format\n   - Structured JSON: See web API handlers\n6. **Version bump consideration**: Per CLAUDE.md, assess if feature requires minor/major version bump and tag during finalize workflow\n\nAll absolute file paths provided above for reference during implementation."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a04abf08efdf617e9 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 73064\ntool_uses: 34\nduration_ms: 58471</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0fd95967-c19b-48b1-b504-9ad5f3e0a46b","uuid":"3097c664-6691-472d-9912-dbdbba0c9c63","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. How `cloche status` command works currently (cmd/cloche/ directory)\n2. The gRPC service definitions (.proto files)\n3. The gRPC server implementation (internal/adapters/grpc/)\n4. The RunStore interface and implementations\n5. The domain types (Run, etc.)\n6. How other commands like `cloche list` work for reference\n7. Any project-related functionality (project settings, concurrency, orchestration)\n8. The version endpoint\n\nRead key files fully. I need to understand the full picture to implement a \"daemon status overview\" feature.","agentId":"a04abf08efdf6